3. Materials Science & Structural Analysis

3.1 Thermal Stress Modeling

Stress in Cylindrical Reactor Liner:
Radial stress:

\sigma_r = \frac{E\alpha}{1-\nu} \left[ \frac{1}{r^2} \int_{r_i}^r T(r) r dr + \frac{r^2 - r_i^2}{r_o^2 - r_i^2} \int_{r_i}^{r_o} T(r) r dr \right]

Hoop stress:

\sigma_\theta = \frac{E\alpha}{1-\nu} \left[ -T(r) + \frac{1}{r^2} \int_{r_i}^r T(r) r dr + \frac{r^2 + r_i^2}{r_o^2 - r_i^2} \int_{r_i}^{r_o} T(r) r dr \right]

Where:

· E = Young's modulus
· α = coefficient of thermal expansion
· ν = Poisson's ratio

Von Mises Equivalent Stress:

\sigma_{\text{vm}} = \sqrt{\frac{1}{2}[(\sigma_r - \sigma_\theta)^2 + (\sigma_\theta - \sigma_z)^2 + (\sigma_z - \sigma_r)^2]}

3.2 Low-Cycle Fatigue Prediction

Coffin-Manson Relationship:

\frac{\Delta \varepsilon_p}{2} = \varepsilon_f' (2N_f)^c

Where:

· Δε_p = plastic strain amplitude
· N_f = cycles to failure
· ε_f' = fatigue ductility coefficient
· c = fatigue ductility exponent (-0.5 to -0.7)

Total Strain Version:

\frac{\Delta \varepsilon_t}{2} = \frac{\sigma_f'}{E} (2N_f)^b + \varepsilon_f' (2N_f)^c

For TZM Molybdenum alloy at 950°C:

· σ_f' ≈ 850 MPa
· b ≈ -0.085
· ε_f' ≈ 0.25
· c ≈ -0.58

Mission Life Prediction:
With Δε_t = 0.002 (from FEA), E = 320 GPa:

0.001 = \frac{850}{320000} (2N_f)^{-0.085} + 0.25 (2N_f)^{-0.58}

Solving: N_f ≈ 15,000 cycles > 500 sols (safety factor ≈ 30)

3.3 Material Selection Criteria

Figure of Merit for Reactor Liner:

\text{FOM} = \frac{k \cdot \sigma_y \cdot \varepsilon_f'}{\alpha \cdot \rho \cdot \text{Cost}}

Candidate materials:

1. TZM (Mo-0.5Ti-0.1Zr): k = 120 W/m·K, σ_y(950°C) = 350 MPa
2. Tungsten (W-5Re): k = 100 W/m·K, σ_y(950°C) = 450 MPa
3. SiC/SiC Composite: k = 15 W/m·K, σ_y(950°C) = 280 MPa

