4. AI Architecture & Control Theory

4.1 Three-Tier Autonomy Framework

Tier 1: Deterministic Guardian

```
IF T > T_max THEN CLOSE H2_VALVE
IF P < P_min THEN INITIATE SAFE_SHUTDOWN
IF ΔP/Δt > threshold THEN ACTIVATE BACKUP
```

Formal verification via Linear Temporal Logic:
□(T > 1000 → ◇(valve = closed))

Tier 2: Explainable AI Optimizer

4.2 Model-Based Reinforcement Learning Algorithm

State Space: s = [T, P, F_H2, F_CO2, y_CO, y_H2O, dP/dt]
Action Space: a = [ΔF_H2, ΔHeater_Power, ΔValve_Position]

Reward Function:

R(s,a) = w_1 \cdot \text{Yield} - w_2 \cdot \text{Energy} - w_3 \cdot \text{Instability} - w_4 \cdot \text{Risk}

Where:
Yield = H₂O production rate (kg/hr)
Energy = Power consumption (kW)
Instability = Σ(Δa)²
Risk = proximity to carbon formation boundary

Q-Learning Update:

Q(s,a) \leftarrow Q(s,a) + \alpha \left[ R(s,a) + \gamma \max_{a'} Q(s',a') - Q(s,a) \right]

With Neural Network Function Approximation:

Q(s,a;\theta) \approx \mathbb{E} \left[ \sum_{k=0}^\infty \gamma^k R_{t+k} \mid s_t = s, a_t = a \right]

Policy Gradient (Actor-Critic):

\nabla_\theta J(\theta) = \mathbb{E}_{\pi_\theta} \left[ \nabla_\theta \log \pi_\theta(a|s) Q^{\pi_\theta}(s,a) \right]

4.3 Explainable AI (XAI) Mathematical Formulation

SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) Values:
For feature j:

\phi_j = \sum_{S \subseteq \{1,\dots,p\} \setminus \{j\}} \frac{|S|!(p-|S|-1)!}{p!} [f(S \cup \{j\}) - f(S)]

Where f(S) = model prediction using feature subset S.

Local Interpretable Model-agnostic Explanations (LIME):
Minimize:

\xi(x) = \arg\min_{g \in G} L(f,g,\pi_x) + \Omega(g)

Where:

· g = interpretable model (linear)
· π_x = proximity measure
· Ω(g) = complexity penalty

4.4 Predictive Sentinel: Anomaly Detection Theory

Autoencoder for Vibration Anomaly Detection:
Encoder: h = f(W_e x + b_e)
Decoder: x̂ = g(W_d h + b_d)
Loss: L = ‖x - x̂‖²

Anomaly score:

A(x) = \|x - \hat{x}\|_2^2

Threshold: τ = μ_A + 3σ_A

Bayesian Changepoint Detection:

P(r_t | x_{1:t}) = \sum_{r_{t-1}} P(r_t | r_{t-1}) P(x_t | r_t, x_{t}^{(r)}) P(r_{t-1} | x_{1:t-1})

Where r_t = run length at time t.

