5. System Integration & Martian Interface

5.1 Cryogenic CO₂ Concentrator Thermodynamics

CO₂ Freezing Point on Mars:

T_{\text{freeze}} = \frac{194.7\ \text{K}}{1 - \frac{\ln(P/5.18\ \text{atm})}{11.3}} \approx 145\ \text{K}\ (-128^\circ\text{C})\ \text{at}\ 0.6\ \text{kPa}

Heat Load for Cooling:

\dot{Q}_{\text{cool}} = \dot{m}_{\text{air}} \left[ c_p \Delta T + x_{\text{CO}_2} \Delta h_{\text{sub}} + x_{\text{H}_2\text{O}} \Delta h_{\text{dep}} \right]

Where:

· Δh_sub(CO₂) = 571 kJ/kg
· Δh_dep(H₂O) = 2835 kJ/kg

Dust Removal Efficiency:

\eta_{\text{dust}} = 1 - \exp\left(-\frac{\pi L d_p \rho_p v}{18\mu}\right)

5.2 Hydrogen Parity Mass Balance Model

Complete System Equations:

\begin{aligned}
\frac{dM_{O_2}}{dt} &= -R_{O_2} + R_{\text{elec}} \\
\frac{dM_{H_2}}{dt} &= -R_{\text{RWGS}} + R_{\text{recycle}} - L_{H_2} + F_{\text{food}} \\
\frac{dM_{H_2O}}{dt} &= R_{\text{RWGS}} + R_{\text{condense}} - E_{\text{H}_2\text{O}} - R_{\text{elec}} \\
\frac{dM_{CO_2}}{dt} &= R_{\text{crew}} - R_{\text{RWGS}} - S_{\text{CO}_2}
\end{aligned}

Steady-State Solution for 500-Day Mission:
Solving coupled ODEs yields:

· Total O₂ required: 84 kg (vs. 773 kg for Sabatier)
· Total H₂ buffer: 10 kg (vs. 105 kg for Sabatier)
· Net mass saving: 1,034 kg

5.3 Power System Integration Equations

Total Power Requirement:

P_{\text{total}} = P_{\text{heater}} + P_{\text{cooler}} + P_{\text{pumps}} + P_{\text{AI}} + P_{\text{ancillary}}

Components:

1. Reactor Heater: 8 kW (for 1 kg/hr H₂O production)
2. Cryocooler: 2 kW (COP ≈ 0.1 at 145K)
3. AI Computer: 200 W (radiation-hardened GPU)
4. Total: ~11 kW continuous

Fission Surface Power Compatibility:
NASA's 40 kWe Kilopower-class reactor can support 3-4 CHRSy-AI units with margin.

