Appendix B: Derivation of Key Equations

B.1 Derivation of Carbon Avoidance Criterion

From simultaneous equilibria:

\begin{aligned}
\text{RWGS: } K_1 &= \frac{P_{\text{CO}} P_{\text{H}_2\text{O}}}{P_{\text{CO}_2} P_{\text{H}_2}} \\
\text{Boudouard: } K_2 &= \frac{P_{\text{CO}_2}}{P_{\text{CO}}^2}
\end{aligned}

Assume H₂O removal keeps P_H2O ≈ 0.1P_CO. Then:

\frac{P_{\text{H}_2}}{P_{\text{CO}_2}} > \sqrt{\frac{K_1}{10 K_2}}

Appendix C: MATLAB/Python Code Framework

Core Reaction Solver (Python):

```python
import numpy as np
from scipy.integrate import odeint
from scipy.optimize import fsolve

class RWGS_Reactor:
    def __init__(self):
        self.Af = 3.16e8  # Pre-exponential, mol/(m3·s·Pa2)
        self.Eaf = 120e3  # Activation energy, J/mol
        self.R = 8.314
    
    def k_RWGS(self, T):
        return self.Af * np.exp(-self.Eaf/(self.R*T))
    
    def equilibrium_extent(self, T, P, n0_CO2, n0_H2):
        Kp = 0.89  # At 950°C
        total = n0_CO2 + n0_H2
        # Solve quadratic from Section 2.1
        a = Kp - 1
        b = -(n0_CO2 + n0_H2) * Kp
        c = Kp * n0_CO2 * n0_H2
        epsilon = (-b - np.sqrt(b**2 - 4*a*c))/(2*a)
        return epsilon
```

AI Controller Skeleton:

```python
import tensorflow as tf

class Tier2_Optimizer(tf.keras.Model):
    def __init__(self, state_dim, action_dim):
        super().__init__()
        self.actor = self.build_actor(state_dim, action_dim)
        self.critic = self.build_critic(state_dim, action_dim)
    
    def build_actor(self, state_dim, action_dim):
        return tf.keras.Sequential([
            tf.keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
            tf.keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
            tf.keras.layers.Dense(action_dim, activation='tanh')
        ])
    
    def explain_decision(self, state):
        # Generate SHAP values
        with tf.GradientTape() as tape:
            tape.watch(state)
            action = self.actor(state)
        grads = tape.gradient(action, state)
        return grads.numpy()
```

