Conclusion

This white book provides the complete mathematical foundation for the CHRSy-AI system, demonstrating:

1. Thermodynamic Feasibility: The catalyst-free RWGS process can achieve >95% oxygen recovery within a defined safe operating envelope (H₂:CO₂ > 5.3:1 at 950°C).
2. Material Survivability: TZM molybdenum alloy predicts >15,000 thermal cycles capability, exceeding 500-sol mission requirements with 30× safety margin.
3. AI Controllability: The tri-tiered architecture provides verifiable safety (Tier 1), explainable optimization (Tier 2), and predictive maintenance (Tier 3).
4. System Integration: The complete mass balance shows 1,034 kg savings over current technology, while power requirements (11 kW) are compatible with planned fission surface power systems.

The mathematical rigor presented herein transforms the CHRSy-AI concept from speculative idea to quantitatively vetted architecture, ready for Phase 1 computational validation and subsequent prototype development.

